Nothing needs to be added to the .gitignore file since only TypeScript source files (.ts) were modified and no build artifacts, dependencies, or temporary files are present in the changes.
```gitignore
# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Build outputs
dist/
build/
.next/
.nuxt/
public/build/

# Logs
*.log

# Environment variables
.env
.env.local
*.env

# IDE files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python
env/
venv/
.venv/
pip-log.txt
pip-delete-this-directory.txt
.tox/
.coverage
.coverage.*
.cache
nosetests.xml
coverage.xml
*.cover
*.log
.gitattributes
.next
.nyc_output
.pytest_cache/
.hypothesis/
.eggs/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg

# Node.js
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
node_modules/
jspm_packages/
web_modules/
*.tsbuildinfo
*.rpt2_cache/
*.nyc_output
coverage/
.nyc_output/
.tamagui/
tamagui-build/
.turbo/

# TypeScript
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

